Another significant event was the coronation of the fourth King of Bhutan on 6 November 2008. It is significant because it was not just the coronation of the King but a conjoining of two important events: the recognition of the end of the reign of the third King I, and the coronation of his son, His Majesty Jigme Khesar Namgyel Wangchuck as the fourth King. Because of this important conjoining of events, the Fourth King is frequently referred to as the people’s monarch who symbolizes the 20th century in Bhutan.

Let's begin in your youth in Thimphu. Tell us, how did you come to the UK?

The United Kingdom formed the biggest part of my childhood when I arrived in this country in 1970. Parents were here and they had a family business. I decided I would love to get a good education at some of the best colleges or schools in this country, but I chose to work at the family business first.
